-- Micron, Five Chipmakers Settle Pricing Claims With States for $173 Million
-- JoAnne Norton
-- 2010-06-24T16:30:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/micron-five-chipmakers-settle-pricing-claims-with-states-for-173-million.html

          
          
             Six makers of Dynamic Random Access
Memory computer chips settled with 33 states for $173 million
over allegations of price-fixing, Tennessee’s attorney general,
Bob Cooper, said in an emailed statement.    
 The companies are Micron Technology Inc., NEC Electronics
America Inc., Infineon Technologies AG, Hynix Semiconductor
Inc., Elpida Memory Inc., and Mosel-Vitelic Corp., Cooper’s
office said.     
          
          


  


        